input:
Alice, Bob, and Claire are friends and avid readers who occasionally trade books. At the start of the semester, they each buy one new book: Alice gets Lolita, Bob gets Catch-22, and Claire gets Moby Dick.
As the semester proceeds, they start trading around the new books. First, Claire and Alice swap books. Then, Bob and Claire swap books. Finally, Claire and Alice swap books. At the end of the semester, Claire has
Options:
(A) Lolita
(B) Catch-22
(C) Moby Dick
